From df7237fba3c05d987b578f85ea3cdb349c23cedc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Faisal Khan <mfkhan@sofi.org>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 01:01:28 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 04/12] feat(rendering): land rendering audit 2026-04
 implementation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implements 27 of the 35 findings from the April 2026 rendering audit
(`.ai/audits/rendering-audit-2026-04.md`), prioritising user-visible
correctness and a11y wins first, then maintainability + future-proofing
nits. A11y, perf, and security are the three throughlines.

Blog post jank fix
- BlogPostComponent's entrance now uses an opacity-only `fade-in`
  instead of `enter-fade-up`, so the View Transitions cross-fade
  doesn't fight a translateY on top of async markdown/Mermaid
  resolution. Loading/error/ready branches each cross-fade.
- BlogPost + BlogList templates moved to `@switch (viewState())` over
  an explicit state machine ('loading'|'error'|'ready' / + 'empty')
  instead of nested `@if`/`@else if` chains.

Perf / change detection
- B3: WebVitalsService.start() defers registration via
  `requestIdleCallback` so the dynamic web-vitals import lands
  strictly after the LCP frame.
- A1: EditorTabBarComponent consolidates fade + indicator updates
  into a single `afterNextRender` block (removes ngAfterViewInit
  double-pass).
- A2: BlogPostComponent hoists nested effect()s out of
  afterNextRender; theme effect now also re-renders Mermaid SVGs.
- A3: NavigationService swaps `computed()` over a static `NAV`
  constant for plain readonly arrays; updates every consumer + spec.
- A4: sidebar `@for` switches to `track item.label`.
- A6/A7: BlogComponent memoizes featuredCover + dims; BlogPost
  replaces canWebShare computed with a one-shot constant.
- E2: BlogPostComponent's related-posts and prev/next nav are
  wrapped in `@defer (on viewport; prefetch on idle)` with
  height-reserving placeholders.

SSR / prerender
- B1: catch-all `**` route flips Prerender → Server (404s no longer
  pin one prerendered HTML to every unknown URL).
- B2: 404 path text is gated on `afterNextRender` so the prerendered
  HTML doesn't bake `curl -I /` into hydration.

Visual / layout
- C1: Mermaid placeholder reserves an aspect-ratio block so the
  diagram swap doesn't CLS the prose below.
- C2: Reading-progress bar drops `role="progressbar"` and is
  `aria-hidden` (it's decorative; ARIA polite never made sense here).
- C4: Removes unused `container-type: inline-size` (paid Chromium
  intrinsic-size cost for zero `@container` consumers).
- C5: Featured/cover blog images now use NgOptimizedImage.
- C6: Hero hoists `[0,1]` skeleton literal to a readonly field.
- C7: Hero gradient text gets a forced-colors fallback so it stays
  visible in Windows High Contrast mode.

Accessibility
- D1: Command palette gets `role="combobox"` + `aria-controls` +
  `aria-activedescendant` plumbing for SR result navigation.
- D2: Sidebar wrapped in `<header role="banner">` landmark.
- D3: Toast region splits role by severity — `role="alert"` for
  `'error'` only, `role="status" aria-live="polite"` for `'info'`
  (the new default). Chunk-load failure flips to `'error'`.
- D4: Hero "latest from the blog" eyebrow promoted to `<h2>` (with
  CSS reset to keep the visual treatment).
- D6: Drop `tabindex="0"` from cert-grid; switch to
  `role="list"` / per-card `role="listitem"`.
- D7: Explicit `aria-modal="true"` on command palette `<dialog>`.

Code quality / future-proofing
- E1: Promotes 5 array-shaped `input()`s to `input.required()`
  (sidebar, mobile-nav-pill, editor-tab-bar, timeline).
- E3: Blog list/post templates → `@switch (viewState())` over an
  explicit discriminant (see "Blog post jank fix").
- E5: TrustedHtmlPipe now requires an explicit
  `source: 'local-markdown'` argument; throws on any other value
  to prevent silent reuse for unreviewed sources.
- B5: `copyToClipboard()` extracted to `@shared/utils/clipboard.utils`
  with cross-browser fallback; Contact + BlogPost now share it.
- B6: Mermaid SVGs re-render in place when the theme toggles
  (source is stashed on the rendered figure for round-trip).
- A5: Hero blog-skeleton template extracted via `ng-template` +
  `NgTemplateOutlet` so loading/empty branches share one source.

Test infra
- ThemeService guards `window.matchMedia` (jsdom doesn't define it).
- WebVitalsService spec uses `vi.dynamicImportSettled()` to drain
  the deferred dynamic-import chain synchronously.
- Clipboard utility spec defines `document.execCommand` before
  spying so jsdom doesn't reject the property.
- NotFound spec replays mocked URL through `NavigationEnd` so the
  post-hydration `liveUrl` path is exercised.

