From e8914ee7140bcc93da01323505d3cc6b6c1015a3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Faisal Khan <mfkhan@sofi.org>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 01:27:52 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 05/12] chore(build): clear lingering errors, warnings, and
 pre-existing test debt
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The rendering-audit work shipped a green typecheck + lint + test combo, but
`ng build` and `tsc` both still surfaced failures predating this branch.
Sweep them in a single pass so the next contributor isn't paying that
attention tax:

- `angular.json`: bump `anyComponentStyle` budget to 12kb warn / 16kb error
  so the legitimately feature-rich `blog-post.component.css` (TOC + share +
  series + author + mermaid + defer placeholders + responsive) clears
  alongside `hero` and `sidebar`. Add the new mermaid CommonJS deps to the
  allowlist (`dayjs` + `customParseFormat` + `isoWeek` plugins,
  `cytoscape-fcose`, `@braintree/sanitize-url`) — they ride lazy chunks so
  there's no initial-bundle cost, just need explicit acknowledgement to
  silence the optimization-bailout warnings.

- `blog-post.component.ts`: guard `rendered` computed against
  `httpResource.value()` throwing when the resource is in an error state.
  The dedicated `error()` computed already drives the user-visible error
  UI; without this guard, every effect tracking `content()` re-raised the
  `HttpErrorResponse` as an unhandled exception during the deliberately-
  failing 404/500 test fixtures.

- `tests/e2e/fixtures.ts`: cast `document.startViewTransition` through
  `unknown` to escape the lib.dom intersection (which is overloaded to
  return `ViewTransition`). The hook only needs a callable function slot;
  the strict signature was rejecting the wrapper's `unknown` return type.

- `skill-badge.component.spec.ts`: the bar fill is now driven by
  `transform: scaleX(var(--badge-fill-scale))` rather than `style.width`.
  Replace the stale width assertion with one that reads the custom
  property the component actually sets, and add proportional-fill coverage.

- `tests/e2e/*.spec.ts`: prettier formatting cleanup on four pre-existing
  e2e specs that were violating the line-length rule.

Verified end-to-end: `tsc --noEmit` clean, `ng lint` clean, `prettier
--check` clean, `npm test` 47/47 files & 404/404 tests with 0 errors,
`ng build` complete with no warnings.

