From f606af48919d5a43441d68121b5423cc7365f029 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Faisal Khan <mfkhan@sofi.org>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 01:31:32 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 08/12] chore(lint): fold prettier --check into npm run lint

CI's lint job runs `ng lint` followed by `prettier --check .`, but the
local `npm run lint` script only ran `ng lint`. That gap is how a
trailing-whitespace regression in homelab-storage-foundation.md slipped
past the previous PR -- it was caught by CI, not pre-commit.

Mirror CI's behavior so a single local invocation gates the same scope:

- `npm run lint` -> `ng lint && prettier --check .`
- `npm run lint:fix` -> `ng lint --fix && prettier --write .` (new)
- `npm run format:write` -> `prettier --write .` (new, pairs with
  the existing `format:check`)

`format:check` is left in place so the PR template's two-line checklist
keeps working unchanged. The new `lint:fix` is the one-shot escape hatch
for "I just want everything green."

Made-with: Cursor
