From 73ddff51b39fe179ee129d5f3d82bdc8588bd4fc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Faisal Khan <mfkhan@sofi.org>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 01:43:54 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 10/12] fix(blog): featured cover overflow + tighten list
 entrance jank
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two related issues on the blog index, both visible on the
"Motion you can feel" featured card:

1) Featured cover bled into the body column, clipping the title and
   excerpt's first character behind the image.

   The featured card uses
   `grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 320px) minmax(0, 1fr)` with the
   figure stretched via `height: 100%` and capped by `max-height:
   280px`. The figure also carried `aspect-ratio: 4 / 3`, and grid
   items default to `min-width: auto` / `min-height: auto`. That combo
   gives the figure an intrinsic width = stretched-height × 4/3 that
   fights the column's `minmax(0, 320px)` cap and pushes the box past
   320px, sliding under column 2.

   Fix:
   - Drop `aspect-ratio` on the cover figure. `object-fit: cover` on
     the inner img already handles the visual crop, and the column
     width × `max-height: 280px` already constrains both axes.
   - Pin `min-width: 0` / `min-height: 0` on `.post-card-cover` so the
     grid track cap wins unconditionally.
   - Pin `min-width: 0` on `.post-link--featured .post-card-body` and
     on the cover img for the same reason (long titles / NgOptimizedImage's
     declared 1600×900 attributes can otherwise inflate their boxes).

2) First two cards felt janky on entrance.

   `.blog-layout` and every `.post-link` both ran `enter-fade-up`, so
   the parent and children translated 12px concurrently — a compounded
   rise. The featured card additionally translated its async-loading
   cover image, which popped mid-animation.

   Fix:
   - Parent `.blog-layout` switches to opacity-only `fade-in` so it
     no longer doubles the children's translate.
   - Tighten card stagger from 50ms → 30ms so the wave reads as one
     entrance instead of a queue.
   - Override the featured card's `enter-fade-up` to use the
     `simple-fade-in` keyframe (opacity-only). The rest of the grid
     keeps the rise; only the heavyweight image card stays still.

   Reduced-motion contract is unchanged — the global
   `prefers-reduced-motion` block in styles.css still squashes
   animation-duration to 0.01ms across all of these.

All comments inline explain *why* (which combination of grid /
aspect-ratio / min-* defaults caused the overflow, and why
parent+child translate compounded).

Made-with: Cursor
---
