-  both .blog-layout and each .post-link translated 12px on enter, which
-  felt like a double-bounce on the first two cards while the featured
-  cover was still loading. Now the parent only ramps opacity; cards do
-  the rise.
+  Entrance choreography is driven by CSS `@starting-style` instead of
+  the `animate.enter` directive. animate.enter adds its class one frame
+  after the element is inserted, which is fine in Chrome (the
+  `withViewTransitions()` snapshot crossfade hides that one-frame gap)
+  but visibly flashes in Firefox, which doesn't support the View
